00:17:45.717 --> 00:17:47.300 align:middle line:84%
The people that own
the building never

00:17:47.300 --> 00:17:49.650 align:middle line:84%
stopped charging maximum
rent the whole time,

00:17:49.650 --> 00:17:50.880 align:middle line:90%
even though he was closed.

00:17:50.880 --> 00:17:52.380 align:middle line:90%
So it was all good to go.

00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:55.460 align:middle line:84%
And then the bank
had a little foul-up,

00:17:55.460 --> 00:17:58.370 align:middle line:90%
and he couldn't get the money.

00:17:58.370 --> 00:18:00.800 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, isn't there
a way to correct it, I mean,

00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:01.940 align:middle line:90%
if the bank made a mistake.

00:18:01.940 --> 00:18:03.410 align:middle line:90%
He said, no.

00:18:03.410 --> 00:18:05.090 align:middle line:90%
He said, I'm sitting here.

00:18:05.090 --> 00:18:07.130 align:middle line:84%
The only value this
business has is

00:18:07.130 --> 00:18:09.490 align:middle line:84%
that these people are
sitting here in the garden

00:18:09.490 --> 00:18:11.240 align:middle line:84%
and I can appreciate
the fact that they're

00:18:11.240 --> 00:18:12.230 align:middle line:90%
enjoying their time.

00:18:12.230 --> 00:18:14.690 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how long I can
keep the doors open for them.

00:18:14.690 --> 00:18:15.120 align:middle line:90%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Right.

00:18:15.120 --> 00:18:16.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm doing
everything I can,

00:18:16.820 --> 00:18:19.040 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't give
me the PPP money.

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:23.810 align:middle line:84%
And that went to corporations
that were getting $50 million,

00:18:23.810 --> 00:18:25.032 align:middle line:90%
they were being given, even.

00:18:25.032 --> 00:18:26.240 align:middle line:90%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Hedge funds.

00:18:26.240 --> 00:18:27.157 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Hedge funds.

00:18:27.157 --> 00:18:29.270 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: With
less than 50 employees,

00:18:29.270 --> 00:18:32.180 align:middle line:84%
but had billions and billions
of in assets and income

00:18:32.180 --> 00:18:34.340 align:middle line:84%
that was stratospheric,
were the first in line.

00:18:34.340 --> 00:18:37.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly, so you
have this really important,

00:18:37.580 --> 00:18:39.223 align:middle line:84%
heart-centered
business that everyone

00:18:39.223 --> 00:18:40.640 align:middle line:84%
was waiting to go
back to work to,

00:18:40.640 --> 00:18:43.430 align:middle line:90%
because he treated them so well.

00:18:43.430 --> 00:18:46.580 align:middle line:84%
And the customers are like
waiting with bated breath

00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:48.470 align:middle line:84%
for the days their
doors open again,

00:18:48.470 --> 00:18:51.560 align:middle line:84%
and he can't see how he's
going to be able, no matter how

00:18:51.560 --> 00:18:53.630 align:middle line:84%
hard he works and
his employees work,

00:18:53.630 --> 00:18:55.053 align:middle line:90%
to really get through this now.

00:18:55.053 --> 00:18:55.970 align:middle line:90%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Yeah.

00:18:55.970 --> 00:18:58.233 align:middle line:84%
The compact is
irretrievably broken.

00:18:58.233 --> 00:18:59.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's broken.

00:18:59.150 --> 00:18:59.390 align:middle line:90%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Yes.

00:18:59.390 --> 00:19:01.057 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I mean,
it hurts everyone.

00:19:01.057 --> 00:19:03.350 align:middle line:84%
And all of us are thinking,
God, can we do a GoFundMe.

00:19:03.350 --> 00:19:05.690 align:middle line:84%
What can we do to help
the cafes stay open?

00:19:05.690 --> 00:19:07.923 align:middle line:90%
What can you do?

00:19:07.923 --> 00:19:08.840 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what do we do?

00:19:08.840 --> 00:19:11.240 align:middle line:84%
This is a good case
in point to talk

00:19:11.240 --> 00:19:14.690 align:middle line:84%
about what can be done for
businesses like this that

00:19:14.690 --> 00:19:17.540 align:middle line:84%
do it right, did it right,
and got screwed where

00:19:17.540 --> 00:19:18.860 align:middle line:90%
the money went to the top.

00:19:18.860 --> 00:19:19.730 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Well,
in the short term,

00:19:19.730 --> 00:19:20.605 align:middle line:90%
I think you're right.

00:19:20.605 --> 00:19:23.510 align:middle line:84%
There's going to have to be
a concerted community, effort

00:19:23.510 --> 00:19:26.960 align:middle line:84%
and that's always been the
gold standard of any economy.

00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:29.390 align:middle line:84%
During the Great
Depression, what worked?

00:19:29.390 --> 00:19:32.090 align:middle line:84%
When people were starving,
when people couldn't

00:19:32.090 --> 00:19:35.240 align:middle line:84%
feed their kids,
they got together

00:19:35.240 --> 00:19:39.390 align:middle line:84%
and they shared what little they
had to make sure that nobody,

00:19:39.390 --> 00:19:42.080 align:middle line:84%
as much as they could-- plenty
of people went hungry, right,

00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:43.220 align:middle line:90%
but people didn't starve.

00:19:43.220 --> 00:19:44.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:44.390 --> 00:19:45.530 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: You know, and
that we could get through it,

00:19:45.530 --> 00:19:48.110 align:middle line:84%
and that was also the time when
we had so-called government

00:19:48.110 --> 00:19:50.450 align:middle line:90%
programs started.

00:19:50.450 --> 00:19:52.250 align:middle line:84%
Soon after that,
Social Security.

00:19:52.250 --> 00:19:53.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:55.250 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Soon after
that, from those abuses

00:19:55.250 --> 00:19:57.680 align:middle line:84%
and those starvations,
especially among elderly people

00:19:57.680 --> 00:20:00.975 align:middle line:84%
among working families, that
created guarantees around that.

00:20:00.975 --> 00:20:02.600 align:middle line:84%
That's where Social
Security came from.

00:20:02.600 --> 00:20:05.250 align:middle line:84%
Medicare and Medicaid kind
of stemmed from that as well.

00:20:05.250 --> 00:20:08.510 align:middle line:84%
So we began to realize that
we cannot have a functioning

00:20:08.510 --> 00:20:11.420 align:middle line:84%
economy if we don't pay
attention to the people that

00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:14.220 align:middle line:84%
create the real value, and
that's a person on the street.

00:20:14.220 --> 00:20:15.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:20:15.020 --> 00:20:16.310 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS:
We've lost that again.

00:20:16.310 --> 00:20:16.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We have lost it again.

00:20:16.730 --> 00:20:18.050 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: And we have
to get back to it again.

00:20:18.050 --> 00:20:20.300 align:middle line:84%
In your case, I would
say, yes, have a community

00:20:20.300 --> 00:20:22.290 align:middle line:90%
rally around this place.

00:20:22.290 --> 00:20:23.588 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Tower Cafe, yeah.

00:20:23.588 --> 00:20:25.130 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS:
And do a fundraiser,

00:20:25.130 --> 00:20:26.850 align:middle line:84%
and let's get that
money if we have to.

00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:27.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:20:27.650 --> 00:20:30.230 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: But let's
begin to put our money

00:20:30.230 --> 00:20:32.840 align:middle line:84%
in our local economies
and not think

00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:36.530 align:middle line:84%
about just making the next
big break in the cybercurrency

00:20:36.530 --> 00:20:37.520 align:middle line:90%
or the stock market.

00:20:37.520 --> 00:20:37.775 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No kidding.

