>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Right.

00:21:30.050 --> 00:21:31.967 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk
about this phenomenon.

00:21:31.967 --> 00:21:32.990 align:middle line:90%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Sure.

00:21:32.990 --> 00:21:36.440 align:middle line:84%
When you break the compact
as badly as it's been broken,

00:21:36.440 --> 00:21:40.580 align:middle line:84%
when people are literally
punished for working harder,

00:21:40.580 --> 00:21:43.640 align:middle line:84%
given more work to
do and not more pay,

00:21:43.640 --> 00:21:45.710 align:middle line:84%
where they're not given
their productivity,

00:21:45.710 --> 00:21:47.670 align:middle line:90%
they go on a kind of strike.

00:21:47.670 --> 00:21:48.690 align:middle line:90%
They get burnt out.

00:21:48.690 --> 00:21:50.490 align:middle line:84%
In America, you don't
even go on vacation.

00:21:50.490 --> 00:21:54.180 align:middle line:84%
You've given two weeks versus
five to six weeks in Europe.

00:21:54.180 --> 00:21:56.415 align:middle line:84%
You're not even given
health insurance.

00:21:56.415 --> 00:21:57.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:21:57.300 --> 00:21:58.740 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: Not
real health insurance.

00:21:58.740 --> 00:21:59.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:21:59.540 --> 00:22:01.570 align:middle line:84%
We don't have, quote,
"socialized medicine."

00:22:01.570 --> 00:22:04.170 align:middle line:84%
>>YIAMOUYIANNIS: So
you're getting paid crap.

